ny way to make it less.<br /><br />And we use<br /><br />        .p2align 4<br /><br />in most of our asm, aling with<br /><br />    #define __ALIGN          .p2align 4, 0x90<br /><br />So all the *normal* functions already get 16-byte alignment anyway.<br /><br />So yeah, it would be less dense, but do we care? Wouldn't the "this is<br />really simple" be a nice thing? It's not like there are a ton of those<br />fastop functions anyway. 128 of them? Plus 16 of the "setCC" ones?<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
